    • Field Detail

      • MAPPED_TYPE

        public static final java.lang.String MAPPED_TYPE
        Added to AttributeSets during putAll(AttributeSet, Map, boolean) and putAll(AttributeSet, String, Map, boolean) calls when there are types provided that aren't natively supported by the AttributeSet. This is used to deserialize to the proper type. If toMap(AttributeSet, boolean) or get(AttributeSet, String) returns a Map with an unwanted MAPPED_TYPE KVP, recursiveRemoveMappedType(Map) can be used to remove it.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
